---
title: Sri Lankan Style Devilled Paneer with Basmati Rice and Homemade Mango Sambol
description: The ‘devilled’ sauce is a common sauce in Sri Lankan cuisine, an acidic hot sauce that’s tomato based with spices and can be served with any proteins. Here, we've chosen paneer to soak up all the flavour! Sambol is a variant of salsa or chutney that's typically used as a topping or side in Sri Lankan cuisine, often being served with every dish.
